  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalSwitch">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a device that opens or closes an electrical circuit in response to a manual or automatic input in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical switch</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">interruptor elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000285">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A gas engine is an engine that uses gaseous fuel as input, employs a spark ignition system, and operates with a reciprocating piston mechanism to generate mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1618"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1616"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1617"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1615"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1619"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor a gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas engine</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Gas engine is defined by constructive characteristics (gaseous fuel, spark ignition, reciprocating mechanism) rather than a unique function. Under Open World Assumption, making these conditions sufficient could lead to false positives where complex hybrid engines or experimental designs with these features are automatically classified as standard gas engines when they might require different maintenance/operational categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas engine is an engine that has gaseous fuel portion as input and has spark ignition system as component part at all times and has reciprocating piston mechanism as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor a gás é um motor que usa combustível gasoso como entrada, emprega um sistema de ignição por centelha e opera com um mecanismo de pistão alternativo para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas engine is an engine that uses gaseous fuel as input, employs a spark ignition system, and operates with a reciprocating piston mechanism to generate mechanical energy.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃f,s,r(GaseousFuelPortion(f) ∧ SparkIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ ReciprocatingPistonMechanism(r) ∧ hasInput(x,f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b318">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b319"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b313"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b241">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b237"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b242"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AgitationFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b57"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b58"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">agitation function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de agitação</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A designed function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the mechanical stirring of a liquid to promote mixing, suspension of solids, or heat transfer.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000185">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1528"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000030"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1529"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A designed function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the measurement and remote transmission of the flow rate of a process stream.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transmissão de sinal de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow signal transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReinforcementLayer">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reinforcement layer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">camada de reforço</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a layer of structural material applied to the wall of a flexible pipe or hose to provide additional pressure containment and mechanical strength.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000113">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electric motor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An electric motor is an assembly that bears an electric-to-mechanical energy conversion function and has both a stator and rotor as essential components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor elétrico é um conjunto que possui uma função de conversão de energia elétrica para mecânica e tem tanto um estator quanto um rotor como componentes essenciais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every electric motor is an assembly that bears an electric-to-mechanical conversion function and has component parts including a stator and rotor at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An electric motor is an assembly that bears an electric-to-mechanical energy conversion function and has both a stator and rotor as essential components.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1164"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ElectricMotor(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricToMechanicalConversionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(Stator(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃r(Rotor(r) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WellheadConnection">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes the mechanical connection between the wellhead assembly and the surface production equipment or Christmas tree.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conexão de cabeçal de poço</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wellhead connection</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Connection"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1404">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WasteGasDisposalFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000334">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor indicador de pressão é um transmissor que mede pressão e fornece tanto indicação visual local quanto transmissão de sinal elétrico do valor da pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure indicating transmitter is a transmitter that measures pressure and provides both local visual indication and electrical signal transmission of the pressure value.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureIndicatingTransmitter(x) ↔ Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(PressureIndicatingAndTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃i(PressureSignal(i) ∧ hasInput(x,i)) ∧ ∃o1(ElectricalSignal(o1) ∧ hasOutput(x,o1)) ∧ ∃o2(LocalPressureDisplay(o2) ∧ hasOutput(x,o2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure indicating transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor indicador de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A pressure indicating transmitter is a transmitter that measures pressure and provides both local visual indication and electrical signal transmission of the pressure value.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure indicating transmitter is a transmitter that bears a pressure indicating and transmission function, has pressure signal as input, and has both electrical signal output and local pressure display.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2579"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1753">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1748"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2072">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2073"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000085"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BrakingElement">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes the component that applies a retarding force to decelerate or hold stationary a rotating element in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de frenagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">braking element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b779">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b773"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2014">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/KnockOutSeparationFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StationaryMachineComponentProcess">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a stator maintains its fixed position relative to rotating components within machinery, providing structural support and housing for electromagnetic windings, guide vanes, or other functional elements that require stable positioning.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de componente estacionário de máquina</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stationary machine component process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a stator maintains its fixed position relative to rotating components within machinery, providing structural support and housing for electromagnetic windings, guide vanes, or other functional elements that require stable positioning.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b63">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MovingVane"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirIntake">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes the opening and duct through which combustion air or instrument air is drawn into petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">admissão de ar</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air intake</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1379">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000275"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000246">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção, permitindo-lhe detectar estados, substâncias ou fenômenos e produzir sinais baseados na detecção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A detector is an instrument that bears a detection function, enabling it to sense states, substances, or phenomena and produce signals based on the detection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A detector is an instrument that bears a detection function, enabling it to sense states, substances, or phenomena and produce signals based on the detection.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Detector(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(DetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b871"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every detector is an instrument that has a detection function and has component parts including a sensing element and signal generation device.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Hub">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hub</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cubo</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes the central rotating boss of a wheel, impeller, or propeller to which blades are attached and through which torque is transmitted.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectrochemicalOxidationProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrochemical oxidation process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de oxidação eletroquímica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A planned process in which a material is oxidised at an electrode surface through an electrochemical reaction, such as in cathodic protection or electrochemical sensing.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ProcessingElement">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">processing element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de processamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a component within petroleum production equipment that performs a specific processing function on the process stream.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CompressionIgnitionSystem">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compression ignition system</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de compressão de ignição</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An assembly of fuel injection and combustion chamber components that initiates combustion by the heat of compression in a diesel engine of petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GasDetectionFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DetectionFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1600"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1599"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas detection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de detecção de gás</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A detection function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the sensing and identification of the presence or concentration of a specific gas or vapour in the surrounding atmosphere.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1011">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnergyDiffusionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b183">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StorageProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b291">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b292"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000124"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FilteredContaminants">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">contaminantes filtrado</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filtered contaminants</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes the solid or liquid contaminants captured and retained by a filter medium during a filtration process.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CombustionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A planned process in which a fuel reacts exothermically with an oxidant to produce heat and combustion products in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de combustão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">combustion process</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b976">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b974"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1177">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConductionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b3436">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WirelineLoggingFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b505">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b506"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b499"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1324">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1325"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000124"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000160">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção wafer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wafer check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b3387"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b3386"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A wafer check valve is a check valve that has a wafer pattern valve body designed for mounting between flanges.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wafer check valve is a check valve that has a wafer pattern valve body designed for mounting between flanges.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção wafer é uma válvula de retenção que possui um corpo de válvula padrão wafer projetado para montagem entre flanges.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wafer check valve is a check valve that has a wafer pattern valve body as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive subtype (both functional and structural aspects). The wafer pattern mounting configuration is a structural differentia that, while characteristic, may have edge cases or specialized variants that should not be automatically classified without expert validation. The structural differentia should be confirmed as both necessary and sufficient in industrial practice before upgrading to equivalent mode.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(WaferCheckValve(x) → CheckValve(x) ∧ ∃y(WaferPatternValveBody(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingFunction">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a SealingProcess and that consists in providing a tight interface against which a closure element bears to prevent fluid leakage through a valve.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1641"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2820"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1642"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2821"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de vedação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sealing function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a SealingProcess and that consists in providing a tight interface against which a closure element bears to prevent fluid leakage through a valve.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnergyStorageMechanism">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a component—battery, capacitor, spring, or accumulator—that stores energy for later release in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">energy storage mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo de energia de armazenamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1433">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LiquidOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1435">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b1436"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000312">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n68ef3b2e7f25472abfe6aab750c8adf8b2166"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">manual actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador manual</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A manual actuator is an actuator that converts human-operated control inputs into mechanical movement or force through direct physical operation.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador manual é um atuador que converte entradas de controle operadas por humanos em movimento mecânico ou força através de operação física direta.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A manual actuator is an actuator that converts human-operated control inputs into mechanical movement or force through direct physical operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ManualActuator(x) ↔ Actuator(x) ∧ ∃s(ManualControlSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ManualActuator is an actuator that has input ManualControlSignal and has output MechanicalPower</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FormationFluidPortion">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">formation fluid portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção de formação de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a portion of fluid originating from a subsurface geological formation and produced through a petroleum production well.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024"/>
  </rdf:Description>
